    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>This was fun, we had to create a 'Free Form Deformation' application for our Maths module at Uni. I also got an opportunity to try my extrude rotate and scale skills in <a href="http://www.blender.org/">Blender 3D</a></p>

<iframe frameborder="0" height="480" width="500" allowFullScreen webkitallowfullscreen="true" mozallowfullscreen="true" src="http://skfb.ly/lk4igec0ba?autostart=0&transparent=0&autospin=0&controls=1&watermark=1"></iframe>


<p>The model turned out ok, although I think I should have made it less cartoonish to allow the FFD app to apply stylised roof.</p>

<p>I made this in Unity, mostly following <a href="http://tom.cs.byu.edu/~tom/papers/ffd.pdfe">this</a> paper by Sederberg and Parry.</p>

